content:
Navigate to an external web address, or within Lightning Experience, Lightning communities, or the Salesforce mobile app from a Navigate Action element on a FlexCard. For example, allow a user to navigate to a Policy record page by clicking an action element on a FlexCard that lists Account Policies.

To create a Navigate Action:

1. Drag an Action element into a state.
2. Under Action Properties, expand the Action link.
3. Select Navigate from the Action Type dropdown.
4. Select a page reference type from the Target dropdown.
5. Configure settings and options unique to your selected Target.
6. (Optional) Specify where to open the target page: Current Window, New Tab/Window.

To create an email link:

1. Drag an Action element into a state.
2. Under Action Properties, expand the Action link.
3. Select Navigate from the Action Type dropdown.
4. Select Email Link from the Target dropdown.
5. Configure settings and options unique to your selected Target.
title: Navigating Pages with FlexCards
